Durban - Police have arrested a 17-year-old minor for an alleged hit and run accident in Verulam on Monday where a teenager was injured and rushed to hospital. According to police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala a case of reckless and negligent driving was opened at Verulam SAPS after the incident which took place  at around 10:30am on Monday where a 19-year-old pedestrian was struck by a vehicle while crossing George Sewpersadh Street in Verulam. "The victim sustained injuries and was taken to hospital for medical attention." She said following the incident police arrested a minor. "A 17-year-old suspect was fined for failing to produce a driver’s license as well as driving unlicensed vehicle. He was summoned to appear in the Verulam Magistrate's Court on September 2." said Gwala. She told East Coast Radio Newswatch: "I would like to warn people who drive without a driver's licenses to make sure that they don't drive vehicles. Parents must make sure that they don't give their children vehicles if they know that they don't have a licence to drive that vehicle. They are putting their lives in danger and the lives of other road users." POST